==English==
===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[Kελτοί]]''' (''Keltee''), from '''[[Κελτός]]''' (''Keltos''), the [[patriarch]] of the Celts, in [[Greek]] mythology a son of '''[[Ηρακλής]]''' "[[Heracles]]" and '''[[Κελτίνη]]''' "[[Keltine]]".

{{wikipedia}}

===Proper noun===
'''Celts''' 

# The various [[Celtic]] tribes who conquered a lot of western and central Europe in the pre-Christian era, originated from modern south Germany and north Austria.

